
Use clip to only show part of the field (values are percentages of the image): 

<frc-field
  game="Charged Up"
  top-left-clip="[20, 10]"
  bottom-right-clip="[50, 80]"
>
</frc-field>


Use <frc-field-config> to create a new field config:

<frc-field name="Custom Field">
  <frc-field-config
    game="Custom Field"
    image="/path/to/custom/field/image"
    width="54"
    height="27"
    unit="ft"
    top-left-corner="[50, 1000]"
    bottom-right-corner="[40, 540]"
  ></frc-field-config>
</frc-field>


Use `rotate` attribute to rotate or flip the field:

<frc-field game="Charged Up" rotation="180"></frc-field>


Add grid to field. Optional grid size (defaults to 1 in whatever unit chosen):

<frc-field game="Charged Up" unit="ft" show-grid grid-size="2"></frc-field>


Add a robot to the field:

<frc-field game="Charged Up">
  <frc-field-robot></frc-field-robot>
</frc-field>